---
description: Treat every published NetScript surface as a JSR-facing contract.
globs:
  - "packages/*/mod.ts"
  - "packages/*/README.md"
  - "packages/*/deno.json"
  - "plugins/*/mod.ts"
  - "plugins/*/README.md"
  - "plugins/*/deno.json"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Public Surface

- Design public types and the README quick start before implementation, following
  `docs/architecture/doctrine/02-public-surface.md`.
- Keep `mod.ts` as a named-export manifest with no logic; split large surfaces into subpath exports
  instead of widening the root entrypoint.
- Use the naming and `deno.json` standards in `docs/architecture/STANDARDS.md`, including lockstep
  versioning and explicit publish include/exclude lists.
- Choose API shapes from `docs/architecture/PUBLIC-SURFACE-PATTERNS.md`: function family, builder,
  abstract base plus concrete default, DSL, or registry.
- Do not re-export upstream packages or test fakes from the root surface; use documented subpaths
  such as `./testing` when callers should import them.
